{"build_type":"library","description":"Remove a single IPM package entirely in one call via dirfd-relative syscalls (no hardcoded paths). Requires the request field root (the packages directory) and name. Opens root then name with O_DIRECTORY (a loose file cannot open as a directory - the packages-only guard), confirms <name>.ipm exists inside (the is-a-package guard), unlinks the .ipm, then unlinkat-AT_REMOVEDIR removes the now-empty package directory. If the directory still holds other files the removal fails and is reported, never silent. Never touches arbitrary files.","module_name":"delete-named-package-source-directory","package_name":"delete-named-package-source-directory","function_definitions":{"delete-named-package-source-directory":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"odir","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":65536},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"atfdcwd","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":-100},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"atremovedir","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":512},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"statsz","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":160},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"dotipm","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":".ipm"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_name","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"name"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name